OL,4,Chuman rights obligations, MPs and
OL,5,Cpeers warn
OL,7,F"Human rights aren't inconvenient
OL,8,Fbarriers that must be overcome to
OL,9,Freach policy goals, they are
OL,10,Ffundamental protections that ensure
OL,11,Findividuals are not harmed by
OL,12,FGovernment action. If a policy is
OL,13,Fsound it should be able to withstand
OL,14,Fjudicial scrutiny, not run away from
OL,15,Fit."
OL,17,FThe Prime Minister's Safety of Rwanda
OL,18,FBill passed the Commons after the
OL,19,FPrime Minister saw off a Tory
OL,20,Frebellion which had sought to toughen
OL,21,Fthe legislation.
