OL,5,Cpeers warn
OL,7,FIt cleared its first major hurdle in
OL,8,Fthe House of Lords last month, but
OL,9,Ffaces numerous amendments in the upper
OL,10,Fchamber and an extended tussle between
OL,11,Fthe Commons and Lords.
OL,13,FMr Sunak has urged peers not to block
OL,14,F"the will of the people" by opposing
OL,15,Fthe Bill as he faces an election year
OL,16,Fhaving made "stopping the boats" a key
OL,17,Fpledge of his leadership.
OL,19,FThe Lords begin detailed examination
OL,20,Fof the Bill in committee stage on
OL,21,FMonday.
